{
  "name": "RPlog_Spycraft_-_The_Planning",
  "title": "Quiet is Loud, Loud is Dead",
  "summary": "In a sealed-off casino back room turned war room, Colonel Eckhart arrives with a squad of marines and duffels of Caspian armor and weapons to plan the rescue of the auction slaves on Nar Shaddaa. The team reviews hand-drawn maps and a projected 3D model of the casino while debating extraction: a commandeered Gamma-class shuttle could hold forty, but they may have to split into teams or pack everyone aboard Tiaryn's Bright Star. Eckhart calls for honest assessments of who can perform stealthy knife work, and Kelnas and Siarra are assigned as Team A to silently eliminate guards ahead of Eckhart's Team B, while the medic Druze is kept protected with the blaster group and Wrexan handles piloting and security feeds. Siarra lays out the full plan: link up after the guards fall, cut the security, free the captives via the cargo lift, load them onto the ships, and jump without clearance, engaging no one. The mission is rescue and exfiltration only, with no demolition and no rescue coming for them if they fail.",
